title: GAT + Generic Const Exprs causes "unexpected bound ty in binder: BoundTy"

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body: Hello! I realize this is the bleeding edge, but I ran into the following compiler bug. If this has already been reported, please link and close - I couldn't quite figure out how to classify this one, so my searching could have been ineffective. Minimal verifiable example can be found here: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=f3b20235fecb30defc4ae3b99b5abbdb ### Code ```Rust #![feature(generic_const_exprs)] #![feature(generic_associated_types)] use std::marker::PhantomData; trait Foo { const N: usize; type Bar; fn foo() -> [usize; Self::N]; } trait Owner { type LendingFooIter<'a, F: Foo>: Iterator where [(); F::N]:; } struct OwnerImpl {} impl Owner for OwnerImpl { type LendingFooIter<'a, F: Foo> = LendingFooIterImpl<'a, F> where [(); F::N]:; } struct LendingFooIterImpl<'a, F: Foo> { _owner: &'a OwnerImpl, _phantom: PhantomData, } impl<'a, F: Foo> Iterator for LendingFooIterImpl<'a, F> where [(); F::N]:, { type Item = F::Bar; fn next(&mut self) -> Option { // * This line requires the `[(); F::N]:` bounds added throughout the above. // * Adding those bounds causes the compiler crash. // * Removing this line and the requisite, above bounds, results in successful compile let _x = F::foo(); None } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0-nightly (7b46aa594 2022-07-05) binary: rustc commit-hash: 7b46aa594c4bdc507fbd904b6777ca30c37a9209 commit-date: 2022-07-05 host: x86_64-apple-darwin release: 1.64.0-nightly LLVM version: 14.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: /rustc/7665c3543079ebc3710b676d0fd6951bedfd4b29/compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/fold.rs:492:29: unexpected bound ty in binder: BoundTy { var: 1, kind: Param("F") } thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Box', /rustc/7665c3543079ebc3710b676d0fd6951bedfd4b29/compiler/rustc_errors/src/lib.rs:1391:9 stack backtrace: 0: 0x7fe295ab9b70 -
